 git reset --hard commitid
=> the changes that are made in the specific commet are deleted.

  git reset --soft commitid
=> it doesnot delete the changes but it keep the file in staging area.

  git reset --mixed commitid
=> it keep the file in non staging area.
   
  git revert commitid 
=> it create a new commit object.where iti doesnot delete the commit history but it removes the changes made in particular commit.but we ca n see what changes are made in particular commit

  git rm --cached filename
=> undo of git add       